<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-10-12T07:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-10-12T07:00:00-05:00" n="778" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d778">
                                <note rend="inline" type="source">765.84/1761: Telegram</note>
                                <head>
                                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Long</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                            State</gloss>
                                    </hi>
                                </head>
                                <opener>
                                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                                        <placeName>
                                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-10-12T13:00:00+01:00">October 12, 1935—1 p.m.</date>
                                        <lb/> [Received October 12—9:30 a.m.]</dateline>
                                </opener>
                                <p>697. My 693, October 12, 9 a.m. Above telegram based on
                                    information available yesterday. Today I learn that in addition
                                    to the French Embassy, the British, German and Belgian Embassies
                                    and the Greek and Egyptian Legations have now received
                                    instructions and have made oral representations. I understand
                                    that with the exception of the Egyptian Legation, which based
                                    its representations on the law of nations, all were based upon
                                    humanitarian motives. Up to now we were the only Government to
                                    make representations as per your 154, October 4, 4 p.m.</p>
                                <closer>
                                    <signed>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Long</hi>
                                    </signed>
                                </closer>
                            </div>
                            </body></text></TEI>